This Privacy Policy describes our policies on the collection, use, disclosure, of information about you in connection with your use of the Muck Rack Services, including (without limitation) all websites, mobile applications and other interactive properties through which the service is delivered (collectively, the “Service”). The Service is owned, operated and distributed by Muck Rack, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (referred to in this Privacy Policy as “Muck Rack” or “we” and through similar words such as “us,” “our,” etc).
This Privacy Policy outlines the personal information that Muck Rack may collect, how Muck Rack uses and safeguards that information, and with whom we may share it. By using our Service or submitting personal information to Muck Rack, you acknowledge that you understand and agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy, and agree that Muck Rack may collect, process, transfer, use and disclose your personal information as described in this Policy. Further, by accessing any part of the Service, you are agreeing to our collection, use, and disclosure of information about you as described in, our
Terms of Service
and our
Responsible Disclosure Policy
. If you do not agree to any of these terms, you SHOULD NOT use the Service.
This Policy applies to all users, including users who are simply viewing content available via the Service, users who have subscribed for the Services, or are contributors of data and/or content via the Service.
This Policy does not apply
to journalists whose information may be available via the Service. Journalists should review our
Journalist Privacy Notice
for more information about the collection, use, and disclosure of their personal information.
